                            <h5><a href="https://www.thejournal.ie/readme/millennials-in-crisis-5136242-Jun2020/">As millennials approach middle age, they face the second recession of their generation</a></h5>
            <div class="byLine">By Amie Lajoie</div>
            <p>
                <a class="excerpt" href="https://www.thejournal.ie/readme/millennials-in-crisis-5136242-Jun2020/">Dr Amie Lajoie says millennials hope the policy of Ireland&#8217;s new government will be anything but austerity, to avoid further damaging an already bruised generation.</a>
            </p>
        </div>
                <div class="post postMini postMiniOpinion">
                        <img src="https://f3.thejournal.ie/media/2019/02/Website-Pic-2-133x133.jpg" height="60" width="60" alt="Jason O'Sullivan" />
                            <h5><a href="https://www.thejournal.ie/readme/covid-19-phase-three-5131485-Jun2020/">Opinion: 'Reopening your business today? Here's the legal advice you need to know'</a></h5>
            <div class="byLine">By Jason O'Sullivan</div>
            <p>
                <a class="excerpt" href="https://www.thejournal.ie/readme/covid-19-phase-three-5131485-Jun2020/">Solicitor Jason O&#8217;Sullivan outlines all the practical steps businesses should have taken ahead of today&#8217;s reopening.</a>
            </p>
        </div>
                <div class="post postMini postMiniOpinion">
                        <img src="https://f1.thejournal.ie/media/2018/09/money-diary-series-river-image1-133x133.png" height="60" width="60" alt="TheJournal.ie reader" />
                            <h5><a href="https://www.thejournal.ie/readme/finances-and-covid-19-5130202-Jun2020/">Money Diaries: A project manager in the north west on €43k who is used to working remotely </a></h5>
            <div class="byLine">By TheJournal.ie reader</div>
            <p>
                <a class="excerpt" href="https://www.thejournal.ie/readme/finances-and-covid-19-5130202-Jun2020/">This week, our reader and her fiancé are busy renovating their home as they prepare for the birth of their first child. They are used to remote working.</a>
            </p>
        </div>
                <div class="post postMini postMiniOpinion">
                        <img src="https://f2.thejournal.ie/media/2020/06/rsz_brian_cremin-133x133.png" height="60" width="60" alt="Brian Cremin" />
                            <h5><a href="https://www.thejournal.ie/readme/phase-three-reopening-5132924-Jun2020/">The three Rs: A business consultant's tips on getting back on your feet and coming out of the crisis stronger</a></h5>
            <div class="byLine">By Brian Cremin</div>
            <p>
                <a class="excerpt" href="https://www.thejournal.ie/readme/phase-three-reopening-5132924-Jun2020/">Brian Cremin of 3SIXTY consultancy says it&#8217;s important that businesses examine all aspects of how they work and adapt fast to meet the new changes.</a>
            </p>
        </div>
